Cherishing the moments I get to spend with this guy one v. one now that Brayden is in school full time 🤍

It’s been such a struggle since this little dude joined our family to find balance between getting things done around the house, splitting my attention between the boys, activities, errands, etc. 

I’ve struggled with an insane amount of mom guilt that I wasn’t able to devote my undivided attention to Drew in the same capacity I did Brayden. 

All the interrupted naps, snatched toys, scraped knees..the fact I rarely got to rock him to sleep as a baby, that I stunk at tracking milestones, and that his first two years of life were all about finding convenient ways to manage the hustle and bustle of every day life.. 

But now, we’re finally getting our time together. It’s been such a joy to slow down and relish in these sweet little moments, and to see life through Drew’s eyes. I’ve waited for these moments for way too long!
